1
00:00:01,110 --> 00:00:07,590
At some time during a bearish move, prices
will start to resist further down-moves.

2
00:00:07,590 --> 00:00:12,379
And when these moves are followed by an ultra
high volume bar, this is a very good signal

3
00:00:12,379 --> 00:00:14,700
to enter into a trade.

4
00:00:14,700 --> 00:00:20,170
When you see an ultra high volume bar, something
is going to happen in the market.

5
00:00:20,170 --> 00:00:25,630
A high volume suggests a high participation,
a lot of interest in trading that particular

6
00:00:25,630 --> 00:00:28,920
area, around that particular price.

7
00:00:28,920 --> 00:00:34,790
The question you must ask yourself is why
there are traders interested in participating

8
00:00:34,790 --> 00:00:38,200
in that zone, what are their intentions?

9
00:00:38,200 --> 00:00:43,580
To answer these questions you have to analyze
the volume along with the price action.

10
00:00:43,580 --> 00:00:47,830
It's about seeing what the price does with
that volume.

11
00:00:47,830 --> 00:00:54,100
Today I will share a very powerful way to
day trade, a scalping strategy more exactly,

12
00:00:54,100 --> 00:00:58,079
using ultra high volume bars, on the 1-min
time frame.

13
00:00:58,079 --> 00:01:07,420
So, like, subscribe, and stick around for
the full video.

14
00:01:07,420 --> 00:01:10,910
The power ultra high volume bar
Stopping volume is a well-known concept in

15
00:01:10,910 --> 00:01:13,230
volume spread analysis (VSA).

16
00:01:13,230 --> 00:01:19,330
It refers to a dramatic increase in volume
that stops the market from falling further.

17
00:01:19,330 --> 00:01:24,140
This is your ultra high volume bar, which
appears after a downward move.

18
00:01:24,140 --> 00:01:28,350
There are many ways to integrate volume with
price action.

19
00:01:28,350 --> 00:01:33,540
But I find that the best technique involves
spotting extreme volumes.

20
00:01:33,540 --> 00:01:38,240
These signals are not frequent, but they are
reliable, showing that professional money

21
00:01:38,240 --> 00:01:44,540
has stepped in and has taken an opportunity
to accept the selling – usually from weak

22
00:01:44,540 --> 00:01:45,680
participants.

23
00:01:45,680 --> 00:01:54,020
Volume Spread For VSA Indicator
One of the main benefits of volume is that

24
00:01:54,020 --> 00:01:59,270
it’s a leading indicator, giving you early
signals when the price movement is going to

25
00:01:59,270 --> 00:02:02,170
continue or reverse.

26
00:02:02,170 --> 00:02:07,740
One of the main principles involving volume
is related to Wyckoff’s law of effort versus

27
00:02:07,740 --> 00:02:08,940
result.

28
00:02:08,940 --> 00:02:13,200
This provides an early warning of a possible
change in momentum.

29
00:02:13,200 --> 00:02:18,950
Divergences between volume and price often
signal a change in price direction.

30
00:02:18,950 --> 00:02:26,650
For example, when there are several high-volume
but narrow-range price bars after a substantial

31
00:02:26,650 --> 00:02:32,900
rally, with the price failing to make a new
high, this suggests that we might have a change

32
00:02:32,900 --> 00:02:35,220
in trend.

33
00:02:35,220 --> 00:02:40,930
This indicator tells us whether the volume
is ultra high,high, low or average.

34
00:02:40,930 --> 00:02:43,980
It’s called Volume spread for VSA.

35
00:02:43,980 --> 00:02:47,750
It’s very easy to read volume using it.

36
00:02:47,750 --> 00:02:54,709
Red means ultra high volume, Yellow – high
volume, Green – average volume and blue

37
00:02:54,709 --> 00:02:56,580
– low volume.

38
00:02:56,580 --> 00:03:02,870
You just need to focus on the red lines, because
these are the ultra high volume bars on the

39
00:03:02,870 --> 00:03:04,239
chart.

40
00:03:04,239 --> 00:03:12,530
The trading plan
Now, the scalping strategy involves fading

41
00:03:12,530 --> 00:03:13,800
the ultra high volume.

42
00:03:13,800 --> 00:03:16,190
Here’s the trading plan.

43
00:03:16,190 --> 00:03:20,879
• The market is decreasing
• Then, it experiences a significant surge

44
00:03:20,879 --> 00:03:22,390
in volume.

45
00:03:22,390 --> 00:03:26,620
This is when an ultra-high volume bar appears.

46
00:03:26,620 --> 00:03:31,819
• After you spot the ultra high volume,
you find the candlestick associated with the

47
00:03:31,819 --> 00:03:33,069
surge in volume.

48
00:03:33,069 --> 00:03:37,930
• Then you simply draw a channel, from the
candlestick’s high and low price

49
00:03:37,930 --> 00:03:44,209
• In theory, the ultra high volume should
stop the price decrease.

50
00:03:44,209 --> 00:03:50,959
• So, the plan is to fade the downward move,
and buy if and when the price goes on the

51
00:03:50,959 --> 00:03:54,610
other side of the channel.

52
00:03:54,610 --> 00:04:00,390
• Stop loss goes below the ultra high volume
candle and the minimum target is a risk to

53
00:04:00,390 --> 00:04:03,470
reward ratio of 2.

54
00:04:03,470 --> 00:04:09,980
But the profit potential is much higher, as
this might be the beginning of a new trend.

55
00:04:09,980 --> 00:04:17,310
Ultra high volume + price action
When an ultra high volume bar appears, after

56
00:04:17,310 --> 00:04:21,220
a down move, what sort of price action should
you expect?

57
00:04:21,220 --> 00:04:26,809
In the best-case scenario, it spots the end
of a short term bear trend.

58
00:04:26,809 --> 00:04:32,340
In this case, the signal will potentially
lead you into the start of a bull trend.

59
00:04:32,340 --> 00:04:38,690
And at the same time, a lot of trend traders
will be trapped on the down side.

60
00:04:38,690 --> 00:04:45,659
At times, instead of preceding a bullish reversal,
it pushes the market into a trading range.

61
00:04:45,659 --> 00:04:51,969
And, of course, there’s also the possibility
that the market will continue to decrease

62
00:04:51,969 --> 00:04:56,289
despite the signal, implying powerful bearish
momentum.

63
00:04:56,289 --> 00:05:02,680
That’s why, to filter bad trades, it’s
better to draw the channel on the ultra high

64
00:05:02,680 --> 00:05:08,289
volume candlestick, and trade when there’s
some sort of activity to the upside.

65
00:05:08,289 --> 00:05:17,780
Narrow Spread Candles + Ultra high volume
A narrow spread candle should have low volume.

66
00:05:17,780 --> 00:05:23,999
However, the ones that are of high or ultra
high volume are special.

67
00:05:23,999 --> 00:05:26,740
This should instantly alert you.

68
00:05:26,740 --> 00:05:33,059
If you have a down candle with a narrow spread
and ultra high volume, then the market is

69
00:05:33,059 --> 00:05:34,909
showing some signs of strength.

70
00:05:34,909 --> 00:05:42,879
As we know, high volume should result in a
wide spread candle, not a narrow spread.

71
00:05:42,879 --> 00:05:44,430
Effort vs result.

72
00:05:44,430 --> 00:05:45,430
Wyckoff.

73
00:05:45,430 --> 00:05:50,490
The sellers are starting to struggle at this
price level.

74
00:05:50,490 --> 00:05:57,330
Equally, if we see ultra high volume on an
up candle then the reverse applies.

75
00:05:57,330 --> 00:06:03,559
Here, the buyers are starting to see signs
of bearish sentiment enter the market.

76
00:06:03,559 --> 00:06:09,979
The candle is narrow, with sellers coming
in, and supporting the market at this level.

77
00:06:09,979 --> 00:06:16,889
Again, this is the first sign of a potential
reversal from bullish to bearish.

78
00:06:16,889 --> 00:06:21,930
Future price action will confirm or invalidate
this premise.

79
00:06:21,930 --> 00:06:28,210
A downward breakout, below the ultra high
volume candlestick is your confirmation to

80
00:06:28,210 --> 00:06:30,930
enter short.

81
00:06:30,930 --> 00:06:35,569
We trade Visa on the 1-min time frame.

82
00:06:35,569 --> 00:06:43,020
I see a range after the market opened and
another down leg.

83
00:06:43,020 --> 00:06:50,630
As price was traded at the previous support,
we see not one, but 2, ultra high volume bars.

84
00:06:50,630 --> 00:06:52,610
And there are narrow spread bars.

85
00:06:52,610 --> 00:06:59,709
By spread, I mean the difference between the
high price and the low price of the candle.

86
00:06:59,709 --> 00:07:05,819
We have our channel, which is right at the
support, the ultra high volume after a down

87
00:07:05,819 --> 00:07:09,449
leg, and 2 narrow range bars.

88
00:07:09,449 --> 00:07:15,800
If price breaks the upper side of the channel,
the plan is to go long.

89
00:07:15,800 --> 00:07:19,340
Stop loss goes below support.

90
00:07:19,340 --> 00:07:22,669
We target the next major swing in price structure.

91
00:07:22,669 --> 00:07:29,069
That’s a risk to reward ratio of around
2.2.

92
00:07:29,069 --> 00:07:39,819
Remember we are scalping, so we want to get
in, with a narrow stop loss, and get out quickly.

93
00:07:39,819 --> 00:07:45,159
When you trade the 1-min time frame, you will
find many ultra high volume bars, but you

94
00:07:45,159 --> 00:07:48,379
won’t trade each signal you see.

95
00:07:48,379 --> 00:07:51,979
Focus on volume bars which stand out.

96
00:07:51,979 --> 00:07:55,389
Here we see a potential signal.

97
00:07:55,389 --> 00:08:00,939
We have an up leg, an ultra high volume bar
and a narrow candle.

98
00:08:00,939 --> 00:08:08,849
A break below the channel, with a very small
stop loss, targeting the previous swing low

99
00:08:08,849 --> 00:08:20,400
offers a decent risk to reward ratio, of around
2.

100
00:08:20,400 --> 00:08:25,939
We have another signal, this time a potential
long trade.

101
00:08:25,939 --> 00:08:33,159
I see a potential double bottom, and an ultra
high volume bar, on a narrow spread up bar.

102
00:08:33,159 --> 00:08:39,070
This isn’t a text book example, because
this is a green candle, and not a red one,

103
00:08:39,070 --> 00:08:45,180
but we are still in a down leg, so if price
is breaking above the high of the candle,

104
00:08:45,180 --> 00:08:48,730
I’ll still risk a long trade.

105
00:08:48,730 --> 00:08:50,880
Which indeed happens.

106
00:08:50,880 --> 00:08:55,050
Stop loss below the most recent swing low.

107
00:08:55,050 --> 00:08:57,839
Take profit at the next major swing.

108
00:08:57,839 --> 00:09:05,490
That’s a risk to reward ratio of around
2.5.

109
00:09:05,490 --> 00:09:15,000
We’ll use the same 1-min time frame, on
euro-yen.

110
00:09:15,000 --> 00:09:22,600
We have a minor uptrend and this is our ultra
high volume bar, which appeared on an average

111
00:09:22,600 --> 00:09:25,399
spread green candle.

112
00:09:25,399 --> 00:09:31,100
The plan is to go short below the channel,
if price breaks it.

113
00:09:31,100 --> 00:09:35,800
And here’s our breakout.

114
00:09:35,800 --> 00:09:43,120
Stop loss above the channel, and take profit
a few points above this support level.

115
00:09:43,120 --> 00:09:53,829
A risk to reward ratio of around 2.

116
00:09:53,829 --> 00:10:00,920
We move to pound dollar.

117
00:10:00,920 --> 00:10:05,410
We see an ultra high volume bar at the London
open.

118
00:10:05,410 --> 00:10:07,649
The candlestick is a high spread one.

119
00:10:07,649 --> 00:10:11,779
So this is a high effort, high result situation.

120
00:10:11,779 --> 00:10:14,800
Not the stopping volume we want to trade.

121
00:10:14,800 --> 00:10:18,689
This looks more like a continuation than a
reversal.

122
00:10:18,689 --> 00:10:28,240
But if price breaks below the channel, we’ll
still risk a trade.

123
00:10:28,240 --> 00:10:32,660
Price indeed went higher, and consolidated
above the channel.

124
00:10:32,660 --> 00:10:40,850
So this was a no trade in the end.

125
00:10:40,850 --> 00:10:43,560
We have another potential signal here.

126
00:10:43,560 --> 00:10:51,939
I see a triple top, a major resistance and
a break of structure right here, which signals

127
00:10:51,939 --> 00:10:56,480
that sellers might be interested in pushing
the market down.

128
00:10:56,480 --> 00:11:02,050
If you saw my previous video regarding the
break of structure, you know this is a perfect

129
00:11:02,050 --> 00:11:06,610
opportunity to short the market.

130
00:11:06,610 --> 00:11:10,850
The signal came after the breakout of this
candle.

131
00:11:10,850 --> 00:11:16,560
Stop loss, as usual, above the channel and
above this previous high.

132
00:11:16,560 --> 00:11:22,120
As a side note, it gives me more confidence
when I see that the signal appeared at a major

133
00:11:22,120 --> 00:11:25,269
intraday resistance.

134
00:11:25,269 --> 00:11:28,860
Take profit at the next swing low in the price
structure.

135
00:11:28,860 --> 00:11:36,000
Again, a risk to reward of around 2.

136
00:11:36,000 --> 00:11:41,250
Again, you are scalping.

137
00:11:41,250 --> 00:11:46,350
And if you’re trading on the 1-min time
frame, there will be lot of noise.

138
00:11:46,350 --> 00:11:51,220
And many ultra high volumes, which might confuse
you.

139
00:11:51,220 --> 00:11:57,519
If you’re using Tradingview, the 3-minute
time frame is a decent alternative to filter

140
00:11:57,519 --> 00:11:58,519
signals.

141
00:11:58,519 --> 00:12:07,990
In this example, we see an intraday downtrend,
and an ultra high volume bar.

142
00:12:07,990 --> 00:12:13,990
The signal appeared at a support level, so
this is an opportunity to scalp a few points,

143
00:12:13,990 --> 00:12:17,379
on the long side.

144
00:12:17,379 --> 00:12:24,300
Price breaks the upper level of the channel
and this is our signal to enter.

145
00:12:24,300 --> 00:12:29,889
Stop loss below this swing low, or below the
low of the day.

146
00:12:29,889 --> 00:12:35,579
And we target this swing high.

147
00:12:35,579 --> 00:12:43,070
Unlucky, we lost this one.

148
00:12:43,070 --> 00:12:47,509
The main limitation of this strategy involves
the market noise.

149
00:12:47,509 --> 00:12:54,139
To reduce it and to reduce false signals,
I advise you to trade ultra high volume candles

150
00:12:54,139 --> 00:12:56,649
during active market hours.

151
00:12:56,649 --> 00:13:03,430
For example, if you’re trading Forex, most
pairs are traded the most between the time

152
00:13:03,430 --> 00:13:09,310
the London trading session begins and when
the US sessions ends.

153
00:13:09,310 --> 00:13:16,020
Volume patterns you see form during low activity
periods,during Tokio session for example,

154
00:13:16,020 --> 00:13:21,240
have a lower probability of working out successfully.

155
00:13:21,240 --> 00:13:27,529
If you trade stocks, you’ll usually see
several ultra high volume candles, right at

156
00:13:27,529 --> 00:13:29,430
the New York open.

157
00:13:29,430 --> 00:13:35,879
I would advise you to avoid trading during
the first 30 minutes, after the open, if you’re

158
00:13:35,879 --> 00:13:41,279
not experienced, and try to find volume spikes
when volatility turns down.

159
00:13:41,279 --> 00:13:47,759
And I’ll say it once again: location of
the signal is very important.

160
00:13:47,759 --> 00:13:54,660
Look for volume spikes around support and
resistance levels, supply/demand areas, Fibonacci

161
00:13:54,660 --> 00:13:59,680
levels or near VWAP or common moving averages.

162
00:13:59,680 --> 00:14:30,699
These are the high probability signals which
will bring you profits.

163
00:14:30,699 --> 00:15:30,570
As always, if you learned something new, drop
a like to show your support.

164
00:15:30,570 --> 00:15:35,269
And check out our Academy program, if you
want to further level up your trading.

165
00:15:35,269 --> 00:15:37,139
Until next time.

